{"_id":"nQ8x5gZhGXFAFW5b","name":"Ranges in Vehicle Combat","permission":{"default":2,"8m8ua3an3okqKvoB":3},"folder":"lVwMcu6yQZ0LZEhQ","sort":500000,"flags":{},"content":"<p>Ranges in Vehicular combat and action act as descriptions of how you are driving and interacting with your adversaries as much as the distance between you. Below are more in-depth explanations for the Vehicular Combat Ranges.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Area:</strong></p>\n<p>It hits everything within Crash range of its target. Everything within Crash range of the target means anything jostling with the vehicle, ramming it, or right next to it.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Crash:</strong></p>\n<p>This is the vehicular version of up close and personal. The crunch and smash of vehicles crashing into each other. If you&rsquo;re jostling with a vehicle, or smashing into it, or if you can look the other driver in the eyes, you&rsquo;re in Crash range. Get up in their grill an make it personal.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Dogfighting:</strong></p>\n<p>Maneuvering and Dogfighting, jostling for the perfect shot. Many fighters fight at dogfighting range, performing skillful acrobatic maneuvers, ducking and weaving through traffic or other obstacles. It&rsquo;s all about getting a clean lock on your target while avoiding their lock on you.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Hold Off:</strong></p>\n<p>They&rsquo;re circling from far off, keeping their enemies at bay. Hold Off is about hit and run tactics, harrying your opponent with long strikes and keeping them guessing. Hold Off is also bombardment with flak or artillery fire before they close range.</p>"}
{"_id":"oBpH1JfJLAb32Ptz","name":"Infiltrador","permission":{"default":2,"8m8ua3an3okqKvoB":3},"folder":"aH3xI2FTz9w7OFVF","sort":100000,"flags":{},"content":"<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Making your Infiltrator</h2>\n<p><strong>Name Choose 1 or make your own:</strong></p>\n<p>Irene, Amanda, Shadow, Mist, Cat, Fox, Sandiego, Drake, Nocta, Parker, Rogue, Yoshimitsu, Kisaragi Description <strong>Choose Pronouns &amp; up to 4: </strong></p>\n<p>Lithe, Compact, Sleek, Nondescript, Sharp, Nimble, Guarded, Quiet, Shadowy, Confident, Competent, Paranoid</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Approaches</h2>\n<p>Assign the following scores to each of the 5 Approaches: +2, +1, 0, 0, -1 . When you upgrade an Approach, increase one of your Approaches by +1 to a maximum&nbsp;of +3. Each Approach can only be increased once.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Signature Move &amp; Background</h2>\n<p>Read your Signature Move and make any choices you need to. Read your Backgrounds and choose one.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Starting Hooks</h2>\n<p>Once all Players have Introduced their characters, fill in at least 3 of your starting Hooks and then choose your favorite 3 to be your current Hooks.</p>\n<p>&bull; [ PC ]&rsquo;s past paints a target on our back. I&rsquo;ll make them leave it behind.</p>\n<p>&bull; [ PC ] and I share a secret that must not be compromised.</p>\n<p>&bull; [ PC ] may be as devious as I am. I&rsquo;ll test their skills to see if they&rsquo;re worthy.</p>\n<p>&bull; [ PC ] might suspect what I&rsquo;ve done, but I&rsquo;ll make sure they can never prove it.</p>\n<p>&bull; I was trained by [_NPC/Group_], When they call on me, I must answer.</p>\n<p>&bull; If I know there&rsquo;s something unique and valuable around, I must have it.</p>\n<p>&bull; I&rsquo;m suspicious of everyone, I can&rsquo;t let a secret stay unknown.</p>\n<p>&bull; I&rsquo;m addicted to adrenaline. I take risks just for the thrill of it</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Itens</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Pistol: 1 Harm, Skirmish, Firefight, Discharge, Stun, Basic Gear</li>\n<li>Shotgun: 3 Harm, Skirmish, Discharge, Messy, Advanced Gear</li>\n<li>Nano Blade: 3 Harm, Skirmish, Silent, Specialist Gear</li>\n</ol>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Calamity</h2>\n<p>When you mark an item in the Calamity list, describe the Fictional consequences mentioned in your choice and mark XP. If appropriate, you may write a Hook about it.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>You get an invitation to a high-class event that offers you a valuable opportunity.</li>\n<li>You requisition or steal a useful or valuable item, choose 1: Tactical Pack, Scanner, A valuable artifact.</li>\n<li>An agent of authority is on your trail, and they&rsquo;re closing in.</li>\n<li>You get an opportunity you can&rsquo;t miss, but you must act now.</li>\n<li>Someone who cared for you when you were vulnerable is in danger and has called for your help.</li>\n<li>You suffer a terrible wound, illness, or debility. Describe what you have lost.</li>\n<li>Now or soon, you encounter an opportunity to make the big score that will see your life&rsquo;s work complete. When you attempt the last big score, roll+Slick. On a 10+, you get in, get your target, and get out nice and smooth. You are promoted to leader of your organization or retire to safety, and cannot continue with the Crew. On a 7-9, you get your target, but it&rsquo;s not clean. You will have to go into hiding for a long time, and can&rsquo;t continue with the Crew. On a 6-, you fail, and die or are captured during the attempt, and are never heard from again.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>"}
{"_id":"pjM6G5bA0Bbt0Rk0","name":"Strengths and Weaknesses","permission":{"default":2,"8m8ua3an3okqKvoB":3},"folder":"lVwMcu6yQZ0LZEhQ","sort":300000,"flags":{},"content":"<h2>+Strengths and -Weaknesses</h2>\n<p>+Strengths and -Weaknesses are tags that signify qualities of a thing like a Vehicle that are true in the Fiction. These Fictional elements will often have mechanical impact on the game; most commonly they will impart Advantage or Disadvantage under certain circumstances. The tags listed below are standard, common ones you can use, but if you customize your vehicle, talk with the SM about custom +Strength, -Weakness, or even Neutral tags that are simple descriptors.</p>\n<h2>+Strengths</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>+Responsive:</strong> It handles well, responding quickly and sharply to its pilot&rsquo;s commands.</li>\n<li><strong>+Speedy:</strong> It&rsquo;s very fast, easily outdistancing slower vehicles.</li>\n<li><strong>+Reliable:</strong> It starts when you want and will perform at its peak right up until it&rsquo;s destroyed.</li>\n<li><strong>+Armored:</strong> It has solid armor that can turn away any amount of small arms fire. You can ram into other vehicles without risking major damage.</li>\n<li><strong>+Spacious:</strong> It has plenty of room and is comfortable to be in.</li>\n<li><strong>+Registered:</strong> You legally possess it and have the required documents to show you do.</li>\n<li><strong>+Inconspicuous:</strong> It&rsquo;s a plain or common vehicle and easily escapes notice.</li>\n<li><strong>+Accurate:</strong> It has a targeting system that assists with aiming any weapons it has.</li>\n<li><strong>+Autonomous:</strong> It&rsquo;s a living animal or simple virtual intelligence capable of moving under its own volition based on a set of simple behaviors.</li>\n<li><strong>+Spacefaring:</strong> It can travel in the vacuum of space, although it doesn&rsquo;t have FTL capabilities.</li>\n<li><strong>+Equipped N:</strong> It has N pieces of Vehicle weapons &amp; equipment. Select from the Vehicle Equipment list.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>-Weaknesses</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>-Sluggish:</strong> It&rsquo;s slow to respond or responds sloppily to its pilot&rsquo;s commands.</li>\n<li><strong>-Ponderous:</strong> It&rsquo;s slower than most vehicles of its type.</li>\n<li><strong>-Lemon:</strong> It&rsquo;s unreliable and may not start when you want, or may break down at an inopportune moment.</li>\n<li><strong>-Fragile:</strong> It&rsquo;s susceptible to small arms fire, and doesn&rsquo;t protect its occupants from attack very well.</li>\n<li><strong>-Cramped:</strong> There isn&rsquo;t a lot of room, it has small and stuffy spaces.</li>\n<li><strong>-Stolen:</strong> You don&rsquo;t own it, and its owners or the authorities may be looking for it.</li>\n<li><strong>-Flashy:</strong> It&rsquo;s showy, unusual, or noisy in a way that draws attention.</li>\n<li><strong>-Inaccurate:</strong> It has unreliable targeting systems, and aiming any weapon is a challenge.</li>\n<li><strong>-Skittish:</strong> It responds unpredictably in stressful or confusing situations.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<table style=\"height: 208px; width: 99.0071%;\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"text-align: center; height: 16px; width: 54.2693%;\"><strong>+Strengths</strong></td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; height: 16px; width: 45.1576%;\"><strong>-Weaknesses</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"text-align: center; height: 16px; width: 54.2693%;\">+Responsive</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; height: 16px; width: 45.1576%;\">-Sluggish</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"text-align: center; height: 16px; width: 54.2693%;\">+Speedy</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; height: 16px; width: 45.1576%;\">-Ponderous</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"text-align: center; height: 16px; width: 54.2693%;\">+Reliable</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; height: 16px; width: 45.1576%;\">-Lemon</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"text-align: center; height: 16px; width: 54.2693%;\">+Armored</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; height: 16px; width: 45.1576%;\">-Fragile</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"text-align: center; height: 16px; width: 54.2693%;\">+Spacious</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; height: 16px; width: 45.1576%;\">-Cramped</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"text-align: center; height: 16px; width: 54.2693%;\">+Registered</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; height: 16px; width: 45.1576%;\">-Stolen</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"text-align: center; height: 16px; width: 54.2693%;\">+Inconspicuous</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; height: 16px; width: 45.1576%;\">-Flashy</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"text-align: center; height: 16px; width: 54.2693%;\">+Accurate</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; height: 16px; width: 45.1576%;\">-Inaccurate</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"text-align: center; height: 16px; width: 54.2693%;\">+Spacefaring</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; height: 16px; width: 45.1576%;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"text-align: center; height: 16px; width: 54.2693%;\">+Equipped N</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; height: 16px; width: 45.1576%;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"text-align: center; height: 16px; width: 54.2693%;\">+Autonomous</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; height: 16px; width: 45.1576%;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"text-align: center; height: 16px; width: 54.2693%;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; height: 16px; width: 45.1576%;\">-Skittish</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>"}
